To get the correct answer to how much surface area there is, the area of each face of the box must be found out and then added to all the other faces' surface areas.

I will now do that.

 

Bottom and top pieces are length • width:

12.5 • 11 = 137.5in²

 

side panels are width • height:

11 • 2 = 22in²

 

front and back faces are length • height:

12.5 • 2 = 25in²

 

There are six different panels and three different sizes of panels, two of each. Now, each answer from before there are two of. Each figure will be multiplied by 2 and then added with the others to find the surface area of the box.

 

(137.5 • 2) + (22 • 2) + (25 • 2) = 369in²

 

The proper surface area of the box is 369 square inches.

22(2)+137.5(2)+25(2)

data_answer: To find surface area you don't multiply the length, width, and height by 2. You add the lateral area with the area of the base multiplied by 2. To find the area of the base you multiply length by width, and to find lateral area you multiply the perimeter by the height. The area of the base is found by multiplying 12.5 inches by 11 inches. The area of the base is 137.5 square inches. To find lateral area you multiply the perimeter of the base by 2. The perimeter is found by adding all the side lengths of the base together. So the perimeter is 12.5+12.5+11+11. The perimeter is 47 inches, so the lateral area is 94 square inches. Now you multiply the area by 2 and add that with the lateral area. (137.5*2)+94=369 square inches. The total surface area of the box is 369 square inches.
